<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<%- include('../partials/new-head', { title: 'Privacy Policy — Kidamame' , url: 'https://www.kidamame.com/privacy/', noindex: true
    }) %>

    <body>
        <%- include('../partials/new-nav', { alwaysScrolled: true, hideNavItems: false, isInnerPage: true }) %>

        <main>
            <!-- LEGAL CONTENT -->
            <section class="legal-content">
                <div class="legal-container">
                    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
                    <span class="last-updated">Last updated: May 29, 2026</span>

                    <p>At Kidamame, your privacy and the privacy of your children are extremely important to us. Please
                        read this Privacy Policy to understand exactly how we handle data when you use our website and
                        applications.</p>

                    <div class="legal-highlight">
                        <div class="legal-highlight-icon">
                            <i class="fa-solid fa-shield-halved"></i>
                        </div>
                        <div class="legal-highlight-content">
                            <p><strong>Our Promise to Parents:</strong> Your child's privacy is our absolute priority.
                                We built Kidamame Discovery to be a safe, enclosed environment. We <strong>do not
                                    collect any data whatsoever</strong> from children: no personal information,
                                no analytics, no tracking. Your kids are safe to explore here!</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <h2>1. Our Apps Do Not Collect Child Data</h2>
                    <p>Our educational apps designed for children (such as <strong>Kidamame Discovery</strong>) are 100%
                        offline once downloaded. We <strong>do not</strong>:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Request, collect, or store any personally identifiable information (PII) from children.</li>
                        <li>Include third-party advertising or analytics networks that profile children.</li>
                        <li>Use Firebase, Crashlytics, or any third-party SDK for analytics, crash reporting, or user tracking.</li>
                        <li>Require you to create an account or sign in to play.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>Any progress or state associated with the app is stored locally on your device and never
                        transmitted to our servers.</p>

                    <h2>2. Platform Crash Reporting</h2>
                    <p>Like all apps distributed through the Apple App Store and Google Play Store,
                        Kidamame Discovery may generate <strong>basic crash reports</strong> handled directly
                        by the device operating system (iOS and Android). These reports:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Are managed entirely by Apple and Google, <strong>not</strong> by Kidamame.</li>
                        <li>Contain only technical diagnostic data (e.g., device model, OS version, crash stack trace)
                            and <strong>do not include any personally identifiable information</strong>.</li>
                        <li>Cannot be disabled by app developers, as they are a built-in feature of the operating system.</li>
                        <li>Help us identify and fix issues to keep the app stable and reliable for your children.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>You can manage your device's diagnostic data sharing preferences through
                        your device's privacy or diagnostics settings. Please refer to your device
                        manufacturer's documentation for specific instructions.</p>

                    <h2>3. Website Information Collection</h2>
                    <p>When you visit our website (<strong>kidamame.com</strong>), we may collect the following
                        information:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Newsletter Subscriptions:</strong> We do not directly collect or process email
                            addresses for our newsletter on our website. Instead, users who wish to subscribe click a
                            link that redirects them to our page on Substack. Your registration and email data are
                            handled entirely by Substack according to their privacy policy, and we do not have direct
                            control over this data.</li>
                        <li><strong>Cookies:</strong> Our website employs a cookie consent mechanism (Cookiebot) to
                            respect your preferences. We only use strictly necessary cookies for basic website
                            functionality. We do not use analytics, advertising, or profiling cookies.</li>
                        <li><strong>Support Inquiries:</strong> If you contact us via email, we will use your email
                            address and provided information only to respond to your request.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h2>4. Data Sharing</h2>
                    <p>We do not sell, trade, or rent your personal identification information to others. Since we do
                        not collect personal data such as email addresses directly through our site or apps, we do not
                        share such information with third parties.</p>

                    <h2>5. Your Rights</h2>
                    <p>Regarding our newsletter on Substack, you have the right to:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Opt-out of any email communications at any time via the unsubscribe link at the bottom of
                            each Substack email.</li>
                        <li>Manage your subscription and data directly through your Substack account.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>If you wish to act on any other privacy-related rights, please email us directly.</p>

                    <h2>6. Changes to This Policy</h2>
                    <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time as our apps evolve or to reflect changes in
                        regulatory requirements. If we make significant changes, we will update the "Last updated" date
                        at the top of this policy and provide prominent notice if required by law.</p>

                    <h2>7. Contact Us</h2>
                    <p>If you have any questions about our Privacy Policy or data practices, please contact us at <a
                            href="mailto:info@kidamame.com">info@kidamame.com</a>.</p>
                </div>
            </section>
        </main>

            <%- include('../partials/new-footer') %>
    </body>

</html>